<title type="html"><![CDATA[Innovations (Bid’ah) &amp; Their Principles • Imam Malik bin Anas [179H] On &quot;Good Innovation&quot; (In Religion)]]></title>

<category term="Innovations (Bid’ah) &amp; Their Principles" scheme="https://forum.salafiri.com/viewforum.php?f=13" label="Innovations (Bid’ah) &amp; Their Principles"/>
<content type="html" xml:base="https://forum.salafiri.com/viewtopic.php?t=1367&amp;p=1451#p1451"><![CDATA[
<strong><span style="font-size: 200%; line-height: normal">Imam Malik bin Anas  On &quot;Good Innovation&quot; (In Religion)</span></strong><br /><br />Imaam Maalik rahimahullah said:<br />&quot;He who innovates an innovation in Islaam regarding it as something good, has claimed that Muhammad ﺻﻠﻰ ﺍﻟﻠﻪ ﻋﻠﻴﻪ ﻭﺳﻠﻢ has betrayed his trust to deliver the message as Allaah says:<br /><br /><em><ul>{This day have I perfected for you your religion}. [Surah al-Maaidah (5): 3]</ul></em><br /><br />And whatsoever was not part of the religion then, is not part of the religion today.&quot;<br /><br /><strong><span style="color: #0000FF">[al-I'tisaam (1/17)]</span></strong><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forum.salafiri.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=56">Shehzad Sattar</a> — Sat Mar 25, 2017 4:25 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
